An Act relative to the 2026 state primary election date.
Whereas, The deferred operation of this act would tend to defeat its purpose, which is to
forthwith establish the date of the 2026 state primary election, therefore it is hereby declared to
be an emergency law, necessary for the immediate preservation of the public convenience.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding section 3 of chapter 53 of the General Laws or any other
2 general or special law to the contrary, a person whose name is not printed on the September 1,
3 2026 state primary ballot as a candidate for an office, but who receives sufficient votes to
4 nominate the person for the office, shall file in the office of the state secretary a written
5 acceptance of the nomination and a receipt from the state ethics commission verifying that a
6 statement of financial interest has been filed pursuant to chapter 268B of the General Laws not
7 later than 5:00 P.M. on Thursday, September 3, 2026.
8 SECTION 2. Notwithstanding sections 11, 13 and 53A of chapter 53 of the General Laws
9 and section 5 of chapter 55B of the General Laws or any other general or special law to the
10 contrary, objections to and withdrawals from nominations made at the September 1, 2026 state
