11 primary shall be filed with the state secretary not later than 12:00 P.M. on Friday, September 4,
12 2026.
13 SECTION 3. Notwithstanding section 14 of chapter 53 of the General Laws or any other
14 general or special law to the contrary, any vacancies from the September 1, 2026 state primary
15 caused by death, withdrawal or ineligibility under section 2 shall be filled by an executive
16 committee, determined by the state party committee, of the same political party who made the
17 original nomination.
18 SECTION 4. Notwithstanding section 15 of chapter 53 of the General Laws or any other
19 general or special law to the contrary, when a nomination is made to fill a vacancy caused by the
20 death, withdrawal or ineligibility of a candidate from the September 1, 2026 state primary, the
21 certificate of nomination shall be on a form prescribed by the state secretary, shall be signed by
22 the executive committee appointed by the state committee of the same political party as provided
23 for in section 3 and shall be filed with the state secretary not later than 5:00 P.M. on Tuesday,
24 September 8, 2026.
25 SECTION 5. Notwithstanding section 28 of chapter 53 of the General Laws or any other
26 general or special law to the contrary, the state primary in 2026 shall be held on Tuesday,
27 September 1, 2026.
28 SECTION 6. (a) Notwithstanding section 135 of chapter 54 of the General Laws or any
29 other general or special law to the contrary, a petition for a recount of the September 1, 2026
30 state primary shall be filed with the appropriate local election officials not later than 5:00 P.M.
31 on Thursday, September 3, 2026 and all recounts shall be completed and notice of the results
32 shall be sent to the state secretary not later than 5:00 P.M. on Friday, September 11, 2026.
